			item: {id: "mmorpg:stone/3", Count: 2b}
		}]
	}, {
		id: "0000000000018015"
		x: 0.0d
		y: 2.0d
		title: "Stamina of the Devoted"
		icon: {id: "paragliders:spirit_orb", Count: 1b}
		description: ["Goddess Shrines are scattered across the overworld — stone structures with a glowing altar at their center. Right-click the altar to pray at it, receiving one Spirit Orb. Each shrine can only be prayed at once.", "Four Spirit Orbs at any Goddess Shrine convert to one Stamina Upgrade. A full stamina bar lets you hold the paraglider canopy open long enough to cross open terrain at altitude without landing once — essential for the Sky Captains chapter's airship builds and for descending from the Aether safely.", "This is optional but strongly recommended before going to The End. The fight with the Ender Dragon involves a lot of elevation changes. Maximum stamina means the paraglider covers descents that would otherwise kill you in a fall."]
		tasks: [{
			id: "0000000000018016"
			type: "item"
			item: {id: "paragliders:spirit_orb", Count: 1b}
			count: 8L
		}]
		rewards: [{
			id: "0000000000018017"
			type: "item"
			item: {id: "paragliders:spirit_orb", Count: 4b}
		}]
	}, {
		id: "0000000000018018"
		x: 2.0d
		y: 2.0d
		title: "Sky Fortress"
		icon: {id: "eureka:ship_helm", Count: 1b}
		description: ["An airship is a base, not just a vehicle. Once you understand the Eureka physics engine, you can build a ship with an internal workshop, a storage room, and enough Balloons and Engines to carry the whole structure. Build it large enough to contain a crafting table, a bed, and a pair of chests — then it's a traveling base.", "Anchor Points let you land cleanly on any surface. Engines give horizontal thrust — more Engines mean faster movement. Balancing Balloon count against structure weight determines ceiling altitude. A heavy ship with few Balloons is a barge. A light ship with many Balloons is an aircraft.", "The practical use: fly to resource sites, anchor, mine, return. Fly to the End Portal entrance with your gear staged on the ship. Use it as a mobile staging platform for the fights in the UV chapter."]
		tasks: [{
			id: "0000000000018019"
			type: "checkmark"
			title: "Build and fly a multi-room airship capable of carrying workshop and storage"
		}]
		rewards: [{
			id: "000000000001801A"
			type: "item"
			item: {id: "eureka:anchor", Count: 2b}
		}]
	}, {
		id: "000000000001801B"
		x: 4.0d
		y: 2.0d
		title: "Five Acts, Five Stones"
		icon: {id: "mmorpg:stone/5", Count: 1b}
		description: ["Act V is the ceiling. Enemy densities and stat scaling are the highest in the Atlas system, and the map boss encounters here are multi-phase fights with mechanics that require specific counterplay rather than just enough damage output.", "Five different Act V map completions — one for each stone rarity tier across the Acts — gives you a milestone view of what Mine & Slash was building toward across the whole pack. The salvage economy, the Orb Forge currency system, the stat soul investment: Act V is where all three of those systems pay off simultaneously.", "After Act V runs, your Mythic Stone supply will be stable. The Nano Reliquary (Tier 6 Orb Forge) and the Orb Forge master machine are within reach."]
		tasks: [{
			id: "000000000001801C"
			type: "item"
			item: {id: "mmorpg:stone/5", Count: 1b}
			count: 3L
		}]
